{"award_age":60.0,"bio_image":null,"category":"Economics","country":"United States","date_of_birth":"1920-09-14T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":"2013-10-20T00:00:00.000Z","gender":"male","image_urls":[],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Lawrence_R._Klein","mini_bio":"<p><b>Lawrence Robert Klein<\/b> (September 14, 1920 \u2013 October 20, 2013) was an American <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Economics\" title=\"Economics\">economist<\/a>. For his work in creating <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Computer_model\" title=\"Computer model\" class=\"mw-redirect\">computer models<\/a> to forecast economic trends in the field of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Econometrics\" title=\"Econometrics\">econometrics<\/a> in the Department of Economics at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Pennsylvania\" title=\"University of Pennsylvania\">University of Pennsylvania<\/a>, he was awarded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Memorial_Prize_in_Economic_Sciences\" title=\"Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences\">Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences<\/a> in 1980 specifically \"for the creation of econometric models and their application to the analysis of economic fluctuations and economic policies.\" Due to his efforts, such models have become widespread among <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Economist\" title=\"Economist\">economists<\/a>. <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Harvard_University\" title=\"Harvard University\">Harvard University<\/a> professor <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Martin_Feldstein\" title=\"Martin Feldstein\">Martin Feldstein<\/a> told the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Wall_Street_Journal\" title=\"Wall Street Journal\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Wall Street Journal<\/a> that Klein \"was the first to create the statistical models that embodied <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Maynard_Keynes\" title=\"John Maynard Keynes\">Keynesian<\/a> economics,\" tools still used by the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Federal_Reserve_Bank\" title=\"Federal Reserve Bank\">Federal Reserve Bank<\/a> and other central banks.<sup id=\"cite_ref-wsj_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Lawrence_R._Klein#cite_note-wsj-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Lawrence R. Klein","place_of_birth":"Omaha, Nebraska, U.S.","place_of_death":"Gladwyne, Pennsylvania , U.S.","text":"Lawrence R. Klein , Economics, 1980","year":1980.0}